    "Note that T5 and MedAlpaca were not fine-tuned so only zero-shot results were provided for reference.",
    "Among the candidate models, Llama-2 generally had the best zero-shot performance, which was consistent in ICL.",
    "While Flan-T5 had a similar or superior performance to Llama-2 across most metrics, it was particularly worse on the RadGraph F1 score (Table 4; Figure 3).",
    "On qualitative review, we noted that T5 provided concise summaries, however important clinical information was missed in this process (Supplemental Table 3).",
    "In ICL, LLMs that allow longer context length (Llama-2 and Zephyr) had the best performance across all metrics when one example was provided (ICL-1)."
